name: hurtResistantTime
desc: Remaining time an entity will be ""immune"" to further damage after being hurt.

name: addedToChunk
desc: Has this entity been added to the chunk its within

name: ignoreFrustumCheck
desc: Render entity even if it is outside the camera frustum. Only true in EntityFish for now. Used in RenderGlobal: render if ignoreFrustumCheck or in frustum.

name: inPortal
desc: Whether the entity is inside a Portal

name: dimension
desc: Which dimension the player is in (-1 = the Nether, 0 = normal world)

name: entityId
desc: A number that uniquely identifies this entity. It is used for server-client communication.

name: nextStepDistance
desc: The distance that has to be exceeded in order to triger a new step sound and an onEntityWalking event on a block

name: fire
desc: The number of ticks left for which this entity will be on fire.

name: firstUpdate
desc: True if the entity is in the first tick of its existence.

name: preventEntitySpawning
desc: Blocks entities from spawning when they do their AABB check to make sure the spot is clear of entities that can prevent spawning.

name: riddenByEntity
desc: The entity that is riding this entity

name: ridingEntity
desc: The entity we are currently riding

name: forceSpawn
desc: If true, forces the World to spawn the entity and send it to clients even if the Chunk it is located in has not yet been loaded.

name: worldObj
desc: Reference to the World object.

name: posX
desc: Entity position X

name: posY
desc: Entity position Y

name: posZ
desc: Entity position Z

name: motionX
desc: Entity motion X

name: motionY
desc: Entity motion Y

name: motionZ
desc: Entity motion Z

name: rotationYaw
desc: Entity rotation Yaw

name: rotationPitch
desc: Entity rotation Pitch

name: slowed
desc: Activated if the dragon is flying though obsidian, white stone or bedrock. Slows movement and animation speed.

name: healingEnderCrystal
desc: The current endercrystal that is healing this dragon

name: ringBuffer
desc: Ring buffer array for the last 64 Y-positions and yaw rotations. Used to calculate offsets for the animations.

name: ringBufferIndex
desc: Index into the ring buffer. Incremented once per tick and restarts at 0 once it reaches the end of the buffer.

name: dragonPartArray
desc: An array containing all body parts of this dragon

name: dragonPartHead
desc: The head bounding box of a dragon

name: dragonPartBody
desc: The body bounding box of a dragon

name: prevAnimTime
desc: Animation time at previous tick.

name: animTime
desc: Animation time, used to control the speed of the animation cycles (wings flapping, jaw opening, etc.)

name: forceNewTarget
desc: Force selecting a new flight target at next tick if set to true.

name: entityDragonObj
desc: The dragon entity this dragon part belongs to

name: blockBreakCounter
desc: Time before the Wither tries to break blocks

name: attackEntitySelector
desc: Selector used to determine the entities a wither boss should attack.

name: isBoatEmpty
desc: true if no player in boat

name: targetX
desc: 'x' location the eye should float towards.

name: targetY
desc: 'y' location the eye should float towards.

name: targetZ
desc: 'z' location the eye should float towards.

name: dropContentsWhenDead
desc: When set to true, the minecart will drop all items when setDead() is called. When false (such as when travelling dimensions) it preserves its contents.

name: fireworkAge
desc: The age of the firework in ticks.

name: lifetime
desc: The lifetime of the firework in ticks. When the age reaches the lifetime the firework explodes.

name: maxArtTitleLength
desc: Holds the maximum length of paintings art title.

name: title
desc: Painting Title.

name: age
desc: The age of this EntityItem (used to animate it up and down as well as expire it)

name: hoverStart
desc: The EntityItem's random initial float height.

name: health
desc: The health of this EntityItem. (For example, damage for tools)

name: itemDropChance
desc: Chance for this item frame's item to drop from the frame.

name: xpColor
desc: A constantly increasing value that RenderXPOrb uses to control the colour shifting (Green / yellow)

name: xpOrbAge
desc: The age of the XP orb in ticks.

name: xpOrbHealth
desc: The health of this XP orb.

name: xpValue
desc: This is how much XP this orb has.

name: closestPlayer
desc: The closest EntityPlayer to this orb.

name: xpTargetColor
desc: Threshold color for tracking players

name: isBlocked
desc: Whether this hopper minecart is being blocked by an activator rail.

name: matrix
desc: Minecart rotational logic matrix

name: turnProgress
desc: appears to be the progress of the turn

name: innerRotation
desc: Used to create the rotation animation when rendering the crystal.

name: fuse
desc: How long the fuse is

name: boltVertex
desc: A random long that is used to change the vertex of the lightning rendered in RenderLightningBolt

name: lightningState
desc: Declares which state the lightning bolt is in. Whether it's in the air, hit the ground, etc.

name: boltLivingTime
desc: Determines the time before the EntityLightningBolt is destroyed. It is a random integer decremented over time.

name: activatorRailCooldown
desc: Cooldown before command block logic runs again in ticks

name: spawnedID
desc: The entityID of the spawned mob

name: primaryColor
desc: Base color of the egg

name: secondaryColor
desc: Color of the egg spots

name: theMerchantInventory
desc: Instance of Merchants Inventory.

name: customer
desc: This merchant's current player customer.

name: recipeList
desc: The MerchantRecipeList instance.

name: objectType
desc: A number that encodes the type of data stored in this entry.

name: dataValueId
desc: id of max 31

name: myEntity
desc: The entity that this EntityTrackerEntry tracks.

name: blocksDistanceThreshold
desc: Track distance in blocks

name: updateFrequency
desc: check for sync when ticks % updateFrequency==0

name: lastScaledXPosition
desc: The encoded entity X position.

name: lastScaledYPosition
desc: The encoded entity Y position.

name: lastScaledZPosition
desc: The encoded entity Z position.

name: lastYaw
desc: The encoded entity yaw rotation.

name: lastPitch
desc: The encoded entity pitch rotation.

name: trackingPlayers
desc: Holds references to all the players that are currently receiving position updates for this entity.

name: isDataInitialized
desc: set to true on first sendLocationToClients

name: ticksSinceLastForcedTeleport
desc: every 400 ticks a  full teleport packet is sent, rather than just a "move me +x" command, so that position remains fully synced.

name: creatureClass
desc: The root class of creatures associated with this EnumCreatureType (IMobs for aggressive creatures, EntityAnimals for friendly ones)

name: isPeacefulCreature
desc: A flag indicating whether this creature type is peaceful.

name: isAnimal
desc: Whether this creature type is an animal.

name: isBlank
desc: When isBlank is true the DataWatcher is not watching any objects

name: objectChanged
desc: true if one or more object was changed

name: heightOffset
desc: Random offset used in floating behaviour

name: heightOffsetUpdateTime
desc: ticks until heightOffset is randomized

name: mobSelector
desc: Entity selector for IMob types.

name: lastActiveTime
desc: Time when this creeper was last in an active state (Messed up code here, probably causes creeper animation to go weird)

name: timeSinceIgnited
desc: The amount of time since the creeper was close enough to the player to ignite

name: explosionRadius
desc: Explosion radius for this creeper.

name: witchDrops
desc: List of items a witch should drop on death.

name: witchAttackTimer
desc: Timer used as interval for a witch's attack, decremented every tick if aggressive and when reaches zero the witch will throw a potion at the target entity.

name: slimeJumpDelay
desc: ticks until this slime jumps again

name: homeCheckTimer
desc: deincrements, and a distance-to-home check is done at 0

name: aggroCooldown
desc: Cooldown time between target loss and new target aquirement.

name: explosionStrength
desc: The explosion radius of spawned fireballs.

name: reinforcementChance
desc: The attribute which determines the chance that this mob will spawn reinforcements

name: conversionTime
desc: Ticker used to determine the time remaining for this zombie to convert into a villager when cured.

name: zombieWidth
desc: The width of the entity

name: zombieHeight
desc: The height of the the entity.

name: angerLevel
desc: Above zero if this PigZombie is Angry.

name: randomSoundDelay
desc: A random delay until this PigZombie next makes a sound.

name: allySummonCooldown
desc: A cooldown before this entity will search for another Silverfish to join them in battle.

name: teleportDelay
desc: Counter to delay the teleportation of an enderman towards the currently attacked target

name: stareTimer
desc: A player must stare at an enderman for 5 ticks before it becomes aggressive. This field counts those ticks.

name: playerNetServerHandler
desc: The NetServerHandler assigned to this player by the ServerConfigurationManager.

name: mcServer
desc: Reference to the MinecraftServer object.

name: destroyedItemsNetCache
desc: entities added to this list will  be packet29'd to the player

name: combinedHealth
desc: the total health of the player, includes actual health and absorption health. Updated every tick.

name: lastHealth
desc: amount of health the client was last set to

name: lastFoodLevel
desc: set to foodStats.GetFoodLevel

name: wasHungry
desc: set to foodStats.getSaturationLevel() == 0.0F each tick

name: lastExperience
desc: Amount of experience the client was last set to

name: currentWindowId
desc: The currently in use window ID. Incremented every time a window is opened.

name: theItemInWorldManager
desc: The ItemInWorldManager belonging to this player

name: managedPosX
desc: player X position as seen by PlayerManager

name: managedPosZ
desc: player Z position as seen by PlayerManager

name: loadedChunks
desc: LinkedList that holds the loaded chunks.

name: isChangingQuantityOnly
desc: set to true when player is moving quantity of items from one inventory to another(crafting) but item in either slot is not changed

name: playerConqueredTheEnd
desc: Set when a player beats the ender dragon, used to respawn the player at the spawn point while retaining inventory and XP

name: mainInventory
desc: An array of 36 item stacks indicating the main player inventory (including the visible bar).

name: armorInventory
desc: An array of 4 item stacks containing the currently worn armor pieces.

name: currentItem
desc: The index of the currently held item (0-8).

name: player
desc: The player whose inventory this is.

name: inventoryChanged
desc: Set true whenever the inventory changes. Nothing sets it false so you will have to write your own code to check it and reset the value.

name: currentItemStack
desc: The current ItemStack.

name: itemStack
desc: The stack currently held by the mouse cursor

name: disableDamage
desc: Disables player damage.

name: isFlying
desc: Sets/indicates whether the player is flying.

name: allowFlying
desc: whether or not to allow the player to fly when they double jump.

name: isCreativeMode
desc: Used to determine if creative mode is enabled, and therefore if items should be depleted on usage

name: allowEdit
desc: Indicates whether the player is allowed to modify the surroundings

name: sleeping
desc: Boolean value indicating weather a player is sleeping or not

name: playerLocation
desc: the current location of the player

name: renderOffsetX
desc: Offset in the X axis used for rendering. This field is {@linkplain #setRenderOffsetForSleep() used by beds}.

name: renderOffsetZ
desc: Offset in the Z axis used for rendering. This field is {@linkplain #setRenderOffsetForSleep() used by beds}.

name: capabilities
desc: The player's capabilities. (See class PlayerCapabilities)

name: experienceLevel
desc: The current experience level the player is on.

name: experienceTotal
desc: The total amount of experience the player has. This also includes the amount of experience within their Experience Bar.

name: experience
desc: The current amount of experience the player has within their Experience Bar.

name: fishEntity
desc: An instance of a fishing rod's hook. If this isn't null, the icon image of the fishing rod is slightly different

name: inventory
desc: Inventory of the player

name: inventoryContainer
desc: The Container for the player's inventory (which opens when they press E)

name: openContainer
desc: The Container the player has open.

name: foodStats
desc: The food object of the player, the general hunger logic.

name: flyToggleTimer
desc: Used to tell if the player pressed jump twice. If this is at 0 and it's pressed (And they are allowed to fly, as defined in the player's movementInput) it sets this to 7. If it's pressed and it's greater than 0 enable fly.

name: xpCooldown
desc: Used by EntityPlayer to prevent too many xp orbs from getting absorbed at once.

name: prevChasingPosX
desc: Previous X position of the player's cape

name: prevChasingPosY
desc: Previous Y position of the player's cape

name: prevChasingPosZ
desc: Previous Z position of the player's cape

name: chasingPosX
desc: Current X position of the player's cape

name: chasingPosY
desc: Current Y position of the player's cape

name: chasingPosZ
desc: Current Z position of the player's cape

name: spawnChunk
desc: holds the spawn chunk of the player

name: renderOffsetY
desc: Offset in the Y axis used for rendering. This field is not written to in vanilla (other than being set to 0 each tick by {@link net.minecraft.client.entity.EntityOtherPlayerMP#onUpdate()}).

name: spawnForced
desc: Whether this player's spawn point is forced, preventing execution of bed checks.

name: startMinecartRidingCoordinate
desc: Holds the coordinate of the player when enter a minecraft to ride.

name: itemInUse
desc: This is the item that is in use when the player is holding down the useItemButton (e.g., bow, food, sword)

name: itemInUseCount
desc: This field starts off equal to getMaxItemUseDuration and is decremented on each tick

name: gameProfile
desc: The player's unique game profile

name: thrower
desc: The entity that threw this throwable item.

name: canBePickedUp
desc: 1 if the player can pick up the arrow

name: knockbackStrength
desc: The amount of knockback an arrow applies when it hits a mob.

name: arrowShake
desc: Seems to be some sort of timer for animating an arrow.

name: shootingEntity
desc: The owner of this arrow.

name: potionDamage
desc: The damage value of the thrown potion that this EntityPotion represents.

name: livingSoundTime
desc: Number of ticks since this EntityLiving last produced its sound

name: experienceValue
desc: The experience points the Entity gives.

name: jumpHelper
desc: Entity jumping helper

name: attackTarget
desc: The active target the Task system uses for tracking

name: equipment
desc: Equipment (armor and held item) for this entity.

name: canPickUpLoot
desc: Whether this entity can pick up items from the ground.

name: persistenceRequired
desc: Whether this entity should NOT despawn.

name: currentTarget
desc: This entity's current target.

name: tasks
desc: Passive tasks (wandering, look, idle, ...)

name: targetTasks
desc: Fighting tasks (used by monsters, wolves, ocelots)

name: equipmentDropChances
desc: Chances for each equipment piece from dropping when this entity dies.

name: numTicksToChaseTarget
desc: How long to keep a specific target entity

name: isSaved
desc: If false, this modifier is not saved in NBT. Used for "natural" modifiers like speed boost from sprinting

name: attributeMap
desc: The BaseAttributeMap this attributeInstance can be found in

name: genericAttribute
desc: The Attribute this is an instance of

name: speedBoosted
desc: Whether the entity's speed is boosted.

name: speedBoostTime
desc: Counter for speed boosting, upon reaching maxSpeedBoostTime the speed boost will be disabled

name: maxSpeedBoostTime
desc: Maximum time the entity's speed should be boosted for.

name: entityHost
desc: The entity the AI instance has been applied to

name: rangedAttackEntityHost
desc: The entity (as a RangedAttackMob) the AI instance has been applied to.

name: rangedAttackTime
desc: A decrementing tick that spawns a ranged attack once this value reaches 0. It is then set back to the maxRangedAttackTime.

name: maxRangedAttackTime
desc: The maximum time the AI has to wait before peforming another ranged attack.

name: deltaLookYaw
desc: The amount of change that is made each update for an entity facing a direction.

name: deltaLookPitch
desc: The amount of change that is made each update for an entity facing a direction.

name: isLooking
desc: Whether or not the entity is trying to look at something.

name: action
desc: The EntityAIBase object.

name: priority
desc: Priority of the EntityAIBase

name: tasks
desc: The EntityAITasks object of which this is an entry.

name: closestEntity
desc: The closest entity which is being watched by this one.

name: maxDistanceForPlayer
desc: This is the Maximum distance that the AI will look for the Entity

name: closeDoor
desc: If the entity close the door

name: closeDoorTemporisation
desc: The temporisation before the entity close the door (in ticks, always 20 = 1 second)

name: idleEntity
desc: The entity that is looking idle.

name: lookX
desc: X offset to look at

name: lookZ
desc: Z offset to look at

name: idleTime
desc: A decrementing tick that stops the entity from being idle once it reaches 0.

name: temptedEntity
desc: The entity using this AI that is tempted by the player.

name: targetX
desc: X position of player tempting this mob

name: targetY
desc: Y position of player tempting this mob

name: targetZ
desc: Z position of player tempting this mob

name: pitch
desc: Tempting player's pitch

name: yaw
desc: Tempting player's yaw

name: temptingPlayer
desc: The player that is tempting the entity that is using this AI.

name: delayTemptCounter
desc: A counter that is decremented each time the shouldExecute method is called. The shouldExecute method will always return false if delayTemptCounter is greater than 0.

name: isRunning
desc: True if this EntityAITempt task is running

name: scaredByPlayerMovement
desc: Whether the entity using this AI will be scared by the tempter's sudden movement.

name: seenEntities
desc: Cache of entities which we can see

name: unseenEntities
desc: Cache of entities which we cannot see

name: attackTick
desc: An amount of decrementing ticks that allows the entity to attack once the tick reaches 0.

name: speedTowardsTarget
desc: The speed with which the mob will approach the target

name: longMemory
desc: When true, the mob will continue chasing its target, even if it can't find a path to them right now.

name: entityPathEntity
desc: The PathEntity of our entity.

name: maxTargetDistance
desc: If the distance to the target entity is further than this, this AI task will not run.

name: villageAgressorTarget
desc: The aggressor of the iron golem's village which is now the golem's attack target.

name: revengeTimerOld
desc: Store the previous revengeTimer value

name: doorBlock
desc: The wooden door block

name: hasStoppedDoorInteraction
desc: If is true then the Entity has stopped Door Interaction and compoleted the task.

name: swellingCreeper
desc: The creeper that is swelling.

name: creeperAttackTarget
desc: The creeper's attack target. This is used for the changing of the creeper's state.

name: leaper
desc: The entity that is leaping.

name: leapTarget
desc: The entity that the leaper is leaping towards.

name: leapMotionY
desc: The entity's motionY after leaping.

name: spawnBabyDelay
desc: Delay preventing a baby from spawning immediately when two mate-able animals find each other.

name: moveSpeed
desc: The speed the creature moves at during mating behavior.

name: mobSpawnerLogic
desc: Mob spawner logic for this spawner minecart.

name: entity
desc: The EntityLiving that is being moved

name: speed
desc: The speed at which the entity should move

name: theNearestAttackableTargetSorter
desc: Instance of EntityAINearestAttackableTargetSorter.

name: targetEntitySelector
desc: This filter is applied to the Entity search.  Only matching entities will be targetted.  (null -> no restrictions)

name: theEntity
desc: The entity we are attached to

name: entityPathEntity
desc: The PathEntity of our entity

name: entityPathNavigate
desc: The PathNavigate of our entity

name: targetEntityClass
desc: The class of the entity we should avoid

name: nearbyOnly
desc: When true, only entities that can be reached with minimal effort will be targetted.

name: targetSearchStatus
desc: When nearbyOnly is true: 0 -> No target, but OK to search; 1 -> Nearby target found; 2 -> Target too far.

name: taskOwner
desc: The entity that this task belongs to

name: shouldCheckSight
desc: If true, EntityAI targets must be able to be seen (cannot be blocked by walls) to be suitable targets.

name: targetSearchDelay
desc: When nearbyOnly is true, this throttles target searching to avoid excessive pathfinding.

name: targetUnseenTicks
desc: If  @shouldCheckSight is true, the number of ticks before the interuption of this AITastk when the entity does't see the target

name: eatingGrassTimer
desc: Number of ticks since the entity started to eat grass

name: grassEaterEntity
desc: The entity owner of this AITask

name: entityWorld
desc: The world the grass eater entity is eating from

name: entityPathNavigate
desc: The PathNavigate of our entity.

name: isNocturnal
desc: friendly is true for iron golems and false for zombies.

name: spawnerMinecart
desc: The spawner minecart using this mob spawner logic.

name: staticVector
desc: used to store a driection when the user passes a point to move towards or away from. WARNING: NEVER THREAD SAFE.  MULTIPLE findTowards and findAway calls, will share this var

name: taskEntries
desc: A list of EntityAITaskEntrys in EntityAITasks.

name: executingTaskEntries
desc: A list of EntityAITaskEntrys that are currently being executed.

name: theProfiler
desc: Instance of Profiler.

name: childAnimal
desc: The child that is following its parent.

name: mutexBits
desc: A bitmask telling which other tasks may not run concurrently. The test is a simple bitwise AND - if it yields zero, the two tasks may run concurrently, if not - they must run exclusively from each other.

name: isSitting
desc: If the EntityTameable is sitting.

name: spawnPosition
desc: Coordinates of where the bat spawned.

name: timeUntilNextEgg
desc: The time until the next egg is spawned.

name: fleeceColorTable
desc: Holds the RGB table of the sheep colors - in OpenGL glColor3f values - used to render the sheep colored fleece.

name: inventoryCrafting
desc: Internal crafting inventory used to check the result of mixing dyes corresponding to the fleece color when breeding sheep.

name: sheepTimer
desc: Used to control movement as well as wool regrowth. Set to 40 on handleHealthUpdate and counts down with each tick.

name: tradeOfferSize
desc: sqrt of (tradeOfferSize divided by 5) used to lower the chance to unlock more trades

name: villagersSellingList
desc: Selling list of Villagers items.

name: blacksmithSellingList
desc: Selling list of Blacksmith items.

name: buyingPlayer
desc: This villager's current customer.

name: buyingList
desc: Initialises the MerchantRecipeList.java

name: needsInitilization
desc: addDefaultEquipmentAndRecipies is called if this is true

name: lastBuyingPlayer
desc: Last player to trade with this villager, used for aggressivity.

name: isLookingForHome
desc: This field will be set to true when a villager gets created by the means of converting a zombie.\nIn next mobTick() it will be set to false and awards all the players in the village with a reputation bonus.

name: headRotationCourse
desc: Float used to smooth the rotation of the wolf head

name: isWet
desc: true is the wolf is wet else false

name: isShaking
desc: True if the wolf is shaking else False

name: timeWolfIsShaking
desc: This time increases while wolf is shaking and emitting water particles.

name: gallopTime
desc: Used to determine the sound that the horse should make when it steps

name: temper
desc: "The higher this value, the more likely the horse is to be tamed next time a player rides it."

name: breeding
desc: This is representation of a counter for reproduction progress. (Note that this is different from the inLove which represent being in Love-Mode)

name: aiControlledByPlayer
desc: AI task for player control.

name: aiTempt
desc: The tempt AI task for this mob, used to prevent taming while it is fleeing.

name: squidRotation
desc: appears to be rotation in radians; we already have pitch & yaw, so this completes the triumvirate.

name: prevSquidRotation
desc: previous squidRotation in radians

name: tentacleAngle
desc: angle of the tentacles in radians

name: lastTentacleAngle
desc: the last calculated angle of the tentacles in radians

name: rotationVelocity
desc: change in squidRotation in radians.

name: trackedEntities
desc: List of tracked entities, used for iteration operations on tracked entities.

name: trackedEntityIDs
desc: Used for identity lookup of tracked entities.

name: entityViewDistance
desc: "Max track distance", measured in blocks.

name: deathTime
desc: The amount of time remaining this entity should act 'dead', i.e. have a corpse in the world.

name: limbSwing
desc: Only relevant when limbYaw is not 0(the entity is moving). Influences where in its swing legs and arms currently are.

name: randomUnused2
desc: An unused random value set in the constructor to a random number between 0 and 12398

name: randomUnused1
desc: An unused random value set in the constructor to a random number between .01 and .02

name: rotationYawHead
desc: Entity head rotation yaw

name: prevRotationYawHead
desc: Entity head rotation yaw at previous tick

name: jumpMovementFactor
desc: A factor used to determine how far this entity will move each tick if it is jumping or falling.

name: attackingPlayer
desc: The most recent player that has attacked this entity

name: recentlyHit
desc: Set to 60 when hit by the player or the player's wolf, then decrements. Used to determine whether the entity should drop items on death.

name: dead
desc: This gets set on entity death, but never used. Looks like a duplicate of isDead

name: entityAge
desc: The age of this EntityLiving (used to determine when it dies)

name: unused180
desc: An unused field that is set to 180 in the constructor of EntityPlayer (and otherwise is 0)

name: isSwingInProgress
desc: Whether an arm swing is currently in progress.

name: hurtTime
desc: The amount of time remaining this entity should act 'hurt'. (Visual appearance of red tint)

name: maxHurtTime
desc: What the hurt time was max set to last.

name: attackedAtYaw
desc: The yaw at which this entity was last attacked from.

name: scoreValue
desc: The score value of the Mob, the amount of points the mob is worth.

name: lastDamage
desc: Damage taken in the last hit. Mobs are resistant to damage less than this for a short time after taking damage.

name: isJumping
desc: used to check whether entity is jumping.

name: newPosRotationIncrements
desc: The number of updates over which the new position and rotation are to be applied to the entity.

name: newPosX
desc: The new X position to be applied to the entity.

name: newPosY
desc: The new Y position to be applied to the entity.

name: newRotationYaw
desc: The new yaw rotation to be applied to the entity.

name: newRotationPitch
desc: The new yaw rotation to be applied to the entity.

name: lastAttacker
desc: The target that this entity is currently attacking.

name: lastAttackerTime
desc: Holds the value of ticksExisted when setLastAttacker was last called.

name: landMovementFactor

name: jumpTicks
desc: Number of ticks since last jump

name: previousEquipment
desc: The equipment this mob was previously wearing, used for syncing.

name: potionsNeedUpdate
desc: Whether the DataWatcher needs to be updated with the active potions

name: entityLivingToAttack
desc: is only being set, has no uses as of MC 1.1

name: entityEggs
desc: This is a HashMap of the Creative Entity Eggs/Spawners.

name: stringToClassMapping
desc: Provides a mapping between entity classes and a string

name: classToStringMapping
desc: Provides a mapping between a string and an entity classes

name: IDtoClassMapping
desc: provides a mapping between an entityID and an Entity Class

name: classToIDMapping
desc: provides a mapping between an Entity Class and an entity ID

name: stringToIDMapping
desc: Maps entity names to their numeric identifiers

name: entityToAttack
desc: The Entity this EntityCreature is set to attack.

name: hasAttacked
desc: returns true if a creature has attacked recently only used for creepers and skeletons

name: fleeingTick
desc: Used to make a creature speed up and wander away when hit.

name: maximumHomeDistance
desc: If -1 there is no maximum distance

name: isMovementAITaskSet
desc: change navigation type when the mob is leeached

name: worldMap
desc: Used to find obstacles

name: path
desc: The path being generated

name: pointMap

This table links axes to cardinal directions. Given an axis and a direction on that axis, {@code int axis, dir;}, the resulting cardinal direction is given by {@code FACINGS_BY_AXIS[axis][dir]}.

axes:
- 0: y-axis
- 1: x-axis
- 2: z-axis

axis directions:
- 0: positive (for the x-axis), negative (for the z-axis)
- 1: negative (for the x-axis), positive (for the z-axis)

name: ROTATIONS
desc:
Represents an array of corners that are ignored when performing a ray trace of a straight stairs block.

The numbers stored in the inner arrays refer to the following corners that will be ignored:

  • 0 - Lower-North-West
  • 1 - Lower-North-East
  • 2 - Lower-South-West
  • 3 - Lower-South-East
  • 4 - Upper-North-West
  • 5 - Upper-North-East
  • 6 - Upper-South-West
  • 7 - Upper-South-East

name: multiplyDeBruijnBitPosition
desc: Though it looks like an array, this is really more like a mapping.  Key (index of this array) is the upper 5 bits of the result of multiplying a 32-bit unsigned integer by the B(2, 5) De Bruijn sequence 0x077CB531.  Value (value stored in the array) is the unique index (from the right) of the leftmost one-bit in a 32-bit unsigned integer that can cause the upper 5 bits to get that value.  Used for highly optimized "find the log-base-2 of this number" calculations.

name: offsets
desc:
Contains the 4KB block offset and number of blocks that each chunk occupies. If a chunk does not store any data, then the array entry contains zero. The format of a non-zero entry in the array is as follows:
  • bits[0:7] , the number of blocks that the chunk data occupies
  • bits[8:31], the block offset of the first byte in the chunk data
The above is specified in lsb first. This array is also written to the region file starting at byte 0.

Note: A block in this context should be understood as 4096 continous bytes in the region file.

name: chunkTimestamps
desc: Contains the times for the latest modification to each chunk. This array\nis also written to the region file starting at byte 4096 (block offset 1).

name: sectorFree

desc: List of random stones to be generated in the Jungle Pyramid.

name: roomsLinkedToTheRoom
desc: List of other Mineshaft components linked to this room.

name: strongholdLibraryChestContents
desc: List of items that Stronghold Library chests can contain.

name: inDesert
desc: Boolean that determines if the village is in a desert or not.

name: terrainType
desc: World terrain type, 0 for normal, 1 for flap map

name: structureVillageWeightedPieceList
desc: Contains List of all spawnable Structure Piece Weights. If no more Pieces of a type can be spawned, they are removed from this list

name: villageBlacksmithChestContents
desc: List of items that Village's Blacksmith chest can contain.

name: theNetherBridgePieceWeight
desc: Instance of StructureNetherBridgePieceWeight.

name: primaryWeights
desc: Contains the list of valid piece weights for the set of nether bridge structure pieces.

name: secondaryWeights
desc: Contains the list of valid piece weights for the secondary set of nether bridge structure pieces.

name: villagePieceClass
desc: The Class object for the represantation of this village piece.

name: ranBiomeCheck
desc: is spawned false and set true once the defined BiomeGenBases were compared with the present ones

name: cropTypeA
desc: First crop type for this field.

name: cropTypeB
desc: Second crop type for this field.

name: cropTypeC
desc: Third crop type for this field.

name: cropTypeD
desc: Fourth crop type for this field.

name: hasWitch
desc: Whether this swamp hut has a witch.

name: biomesForGeneration
desc: The biomes that are used to generate the chunk

name: noiseGen5
desc: A NoiseGeneratorOctaves used in generating terrain

name: noiseGen6
desc: A NoiseGeneratorOctaves used in generating terrain

name: rand
desc: RNG.

name: worldObj
desc: Reference to the World object.

name: mapFeaturesEnabled
desc: are map structures going to be generated (e.g. strongholds)

name: strongholdGenerator
desc: Holds Stronghold Generator

name: villageGenerator
desc: Holds Village Generator

name: mineshaftGenerator
desc: Holds Mineshaft Generator

name: ravineGenerator
desc: Holds ravine generator

name: biomesForGeneration
desc: The biomes that are used to generate the chunk

name: flatLayers
desc: List of layers on this preset.

name: worldFeatures
desc: List of world features enabled on this preset.

name: isFlaming
desc: whether or not the explosion sets fire to blocks around it

name: isSmoking
desc: whether or not this explosion spawns smoke particles

name: affectedBlockPositions
desc: A list of ChunkPositions of blocks affected by this explosion

name: playerKnockbackMap
desc: Maps players to the knockback vector applied by the explosion, to send to the client

name: xCoord
desc: X position this tick is occuring at

name: yCoord
desc: Y position this tick is occuring at

name: zCoord
desc: Z position this tick is occuring at

name: scheduledTime
desc: Time this tick is scheduled to occur at

name: nextTickEntryID
desc: The id number for the next tick entry

name: tickEntryID
desc: The id of the tick entry

name: theEntityTracker
desc: The entity tracker for this server world.

name: thePlayerManager
desc: The player chunk map for this server world.

name: pendingTickListEntriesTreeSet
desc: All work to do in future ticks.

name: allPlayersSleeping
desc: is false if there are no players

name: worldTeleporter
desc: the teleporter to use when the entity is being transferred into the dimension

name: entityIdMap
desc: An IntHashMap of entity IDs (integers) to their Entity objects.

name: levelSaving
desc: Whether or not level saving is enabled

name: worldObj
desc: world object being used

name: worldChunkMgr
desc: World chunk manager being used to generate chunks

name: isHellWorld
desc: States whether the Hell world provider is used(true) or if the normal world provider is used(false)

name: hasNoSky
desc: A boolean that tells if a world does not have a sky. Used in calculating weather and skylight

name: lightBrightnessTable
desc: Light to brightness conversion table

name: dimensionId
desc: The id for the dimension (ex. -1: Nether, 0: Overworld, 1: The End)

name: colorsSunriseSunset
desc: Array for sunrise/sunset colors (RGBA)

name: isRemote
desc: This is set to true for client worlds, and false for server worlds.

name: activeChunkSet
desc: Positions to update

name: spawnHostileMobs
desc: indicates if enemies are spawned or not

name: spawnPeacefulMobs
desc: A flag indicating whether we should spawn peaceful mobs.

name: lightUpdateBlockList
desc: is a temporary list of blocks and light values used when updating light levels. Holds up to 32x32x32 blocks (the maximum influence of a light source.) Every element is a packed bit value: 0000000000LLLLzzzzzzyyyyyyxxxxxx. The 4-bit L is a light level used when darkening blocks. 6-bit numbers x, y and z represent the block's offset from the original block, plus 32 (i.e. value of 31 would mean a -1 offset

name: ambientTickCountdown
desc: number of ticks until the next random ambients play

name: processingLoadedTiles
desc: True while the World is ticking {@link #tickableTileEntities}, to prevent CME's if any of those ticks create more tile entities.

name: addedTileEntityList
desc: Tile Entity additions that were deferred because the World was still iterating existing Tile Entities; will be added to the world at the end of the tick.

name: tileEntitiesToBeRemoved
desc: Tile Entity removals that were deferred because the World was still iterating existing Tile Entities; will be removed from the world at the end of the tick.

name: scheduledUpdatesAreImmediate
desc: boolean; if true updates scheduled by scheduleBlockUpdate happen immediately

name: loadedEntityList
desc: A list of all Entities in all currently-loaded chunks

name: loadedTileEntityList
desc: A list of the loaded tile entities in the world

name: playerEntities
desc: Array list of players in the world.

name: weatherEffects
desc: a list of all the lightning entities

name: skylightSubtracted
desc: How much light is subtracted from full daylight

name: updateLCG
desc: Contains the current Linear Congruential Generator seed for block updates. Used with an A value of 3 and a C value of 0x3c6ef35f, producing a highly planar series of values ill-suited for choosing random blocks in a 16x128x16 field.

name: DIST_HASH_MAGIC
desc: magic number used to generate fast random numbers for 3d distribution within a chunk

name: lastLightningBolt
desc: Set to 2 whenever a lightning bolt is generated in SSP. Decrements if > 0 in updateWeather(). Value appears to be unused.

name: difficultySetting
desc: Option > Difficulty setting (0 - 3)

name: rand
desc: RNG for World.

name: provider
desc: The WorldProvider instance that World uses.

name: chunkProvider
desc: Handles chunk operations and caching

name: worldInfo
desc: holds information about a world (size on disk, time, spawn point, seed, ...)

name: findingSpawnPoint
desc: Boolean that is set to true when trying to find a spawn point

name: theWorld
desc: Reference to the World object.

name: mcServer
desc: Reference to the MinecraftServer object.

name: theWorldServer
desc: The WorldServer object.

name: random
desc: A private Random() function in Teleporter

name: destinationCoordinateCache
desc: Stores successful portal placement locations for rapid lookup.

name: destinationCoordinateKeys
desc: A list of valid keys for the destinationCoordainteCache. These are based on the X & Z of the players initial location.

name: foliageBuffer
desc: Color buffer for foliage

name: dirty
desc: Whether this MapDataBase needs saving to disk.

name: mapName
desc: The name of the map data nbt

name: worldTypes
desc: List of world types.

name: DEFAULT
desc: Default world type.

name: FLAT
desc: Flat world type.

name: LARGE_BIOMES
desc: Large Biome world Type.

name: AMPLIFIED
desc: amplified world type

name: DEFAULT_1_1
desc: Default (1.1) world type.

name: worldTypeId
desc: ID for this world type.

name: worldType
desc: 'default' or 'flat'

name: generatorVersion
desc: The int version of the ChunkProvider that generated this world.

name: canBeCreated
desc: Whether this world type can be generated. Normally true; set to false for out-of-date generator versions.

name: isWorldTypeVersioned
desc: Whether this WorldType has a version or not.

name: grassBuffer
desc: Color buffer for grass

name: lastUpdateTime
desc: The worldtime at which this PortalPosition was last verified

name: teleporterInstance
desc: The teleporter to which this PortalPosition applies
